# Game Implementation Guidelines

## Game Board
- Implement the game board as a 2D grid (List<List<Block>>)
- Support both 6x6 and 8x8 grid sizes
- Ensure blocks have properties for color, position, and selection state

## Block Matching Logic
- Two blocks can only be selected if they are adjacent (horizontally or vertically)
- Selected blocks must match one of the four available templates by:
  1. Color combination
  2. Order/sequence
  3. Orientation (horizontal or vertical)
- Templates are displayed at the bottom of the screen
- Matched blocks are permanently removed (no refilling)

## Game State Management
- Track the current level, moves, and time
- Detect win condition: all blocks cleared
- Detect loss condition: no possible matches with current templates
- Implement undo functionality for reverting the last move
- Implement shuffle functionality to rearrange remaining blocks

## Persistence
- Save game progress using shared_preferences
- Store player statistics (games played, win rate, best times)
- Save unlocked levels and achievements
- Maintain leaderboard data locally

## UI Interactions
- Implement intuitive block selection with visual feedback
- Show clear indicators for matched templates
- Provide smooth animations for block removal
- Include helpful tooltips or guides for new players